column1: [iOS] Loans -- BBPS Logo Placements
column31:
*What is this about?*

The branding guidelines of BBPS (from NPCI) suggest that we must show relevant BBPS logos at certain points in the loan addition & payment journey. The app goes through an extensive review of the implementation of these design/branding guidelines to be allowed to use BBPS APIs. The same has been detailed in this ticket. 


Logos have been updated in this Figma [https://www.figma.com/file/WYXns2yEh0IrSalDJ9Lor1/V2-Production-Ready?node-id=1760%3A247134&t=E2qhSYusIK2BnlQA-4|https://www.figma.com/file/WYXns2yEh0IrSalDJ9Lor1/V2-Production-Ready?node-id=1760%3A247134&t=E2qhSYusIK2BnlQA-4|smart-link]. Please refer to screens with details below for more information. 



*Screen 1 - Select Your Loan Provider*

Show the B mnemonic (24x24) and Bharat Billpay logo (48x16)

!image-20221220-113911.png|width=375,height=812!



*Screen 2 - Enter Your Loan Details*

Horizonal Bharat Billpay logo (48x16) on top-right and vertical Bharat Billpay logo (17x24) with consent

!image-20221220-114153.png|width=375,height=1052!

*Screen 3 - Loan Added Successfully*

Horizontal Bharat Billpay logo (48x16) on top right 

!image-20221220-114536.png|width=375,height=812!

*Screen 4 - Loan Payment Successful*

B Assured logo (30x30) next to Transaction Details text 

!image-20221220-114814.png|width=375,height=380!

column1: Android Handle loan details in Transaction details
IOS Handle loan details in Transaction details
[iOS/Android] - [BBPS Loans] Discovery of BBPS Loans and auto-fetch of Loan Bill Details
column31:
Experian is providing the Loan Account Number as unmasked. 



If the customer gets onboarded and we have identified loans which are under BBPS category and only loan account number is required to fetch the bill, we need to call the bill fetch API and if bill due amount is identified(greater than 0), product should be created with all the required details.



If the identified loan require additional information from the customer to fetch the bill, the customer will manually add those loans from Add Product section.

column1: [IOS] Instabug SDK Integration
column31:
*About Instabug SDK Integration:* [*Overview (instabug.com)*|https://docs.instabug.com/docs/ios-overview]

Instabug is a mobile application debugging and feedback tool for iOS and Android apps. It allows developers to capture and report bugs, crashes, and other issues in their apps, as well as gather user feedback and feature requests. Instabug provides a set of tools that can be integrated into a mobile app to enable users to report problems directly from within the app. These tools include a bug reporting tool, in-app surveys, and a feedback forum. Instabug aims to help developers improve the quality and user experience of their apps by making it easier for them to identify and fix issues, and to gather valuable user insights.

*SDK Integration:* [*Integrating Instabug*|https://docs.instabug.com/docs/ios-integration] *- IOS*

For integrating we have the App token mentioned below:

!image-20221216-160537.png|width=100%!

{noformat}Live App "APP_TOKEN" = f4e9345e4567b35a0402421157b5e1ba{noformat}

{noformat}Beta App "APP_TOKEN" = 1642056e745d5e6124d2be070b4e5138{noformat}

*SDK Configuration:* [*SDK Customizations (instabug.com)*|https://docs.instabug.com/docs/android-user-experience]

We want the following SDK customisation:

A) We need the SDK to be Invoked when the device is shaken, or a screenshot is taken. Below is the code snippet for the same:

{code:swift}#if DEBUG
Instabug.start(withToken: "YOUR-TOKEN-HERE", invocationEvents: [.shake, .screenshot])
#endif{code}

B) We need to turn off the prompt that pops up when the SDK is invoked. For that, we will use the below-mentioned code snippet:

{code:swift}// Disable the Bugs, Feedback, & Questions. If disabled, "Report a problem" "Suggest an improvement" & "Ask a Question" are removed from the Instabug's prompt, and manually showing the bug reporting or feedback doesn't have an effect.
BugReporting.enabled = false{code}

Other Prompt Modifications are mentioned below:

{code:swift}// Disable the Bugs, Feedback, & Questions. If disabled, "Report a problem" "Suggest an improvement" & "Ask a Question" are removed from the Instabug's prompt, and manually showing the bug reporting or feedback doesn't have an effect.
BugReporting.enabled = false

// Specify which of the feedback, bug, or question options appear in the prompt options
BugReporting.promptOptionsEnabledReportTypes = [.bug, .feedback, .question]

// Disable the Replies. If disabled, the chats list button is removed from Instabug's prompt, the in-app notifications are disabled, and manually showing the chats list doesn't have an effect. 
Replies.enabled = false{code}



*Expectation of the SDK integration:* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZFSy5nrZn20|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZFSy5nrZn20|smart-link]

When a user shakes device or takes screenshot, it should trigger the Instabug SDK and take to the following form shown in below picture:

!Wio0dwWWmQuBUWiWcovOBo5ssPawyFJm9qoQZZJXd-KbmncfuxqrVLSRWFdjS_hA3pP0D_5GDzmOJDj5V8ph3XmXE7lWS1ixUWwbOjLvbMqrR-7kTaGba1QfjdRiNQ7c1J_KKBvawl2Qb_4JWPnqJhKzMqwWaGCeZUfZHlCOm0qnoadA-FYGTqHFOY6SHQ|width=1600,height=1000!

column1: [iOS] Home -- Show all products supported on CheQ on top widget
column31:
All scenarios have been added here [https://www.figma.com/file/WYXns2yEh0IrSalDJ9Lor1/V2-Production-Ready?node-id=1760%3A230403&t=nVtepJzIyxAQyiEz-4|https://www.figma.com/file/WYXns2yEh0IrSalDJ9Lor1/V2-Production-Ready?node-id=1760%3A230403&t=nVtepJzIyxAQyiEz-4|smart-link]

Expectation:

* If a product is supported by CheQ, show them on the top widget of the Home Tab
* If products are found, for each individual product:
** where bill is found, 
*** show the amount due + when it is due
** where bill is not found
*** show “no bill found”
* If no products are found for the user, show the nudge
* CTAs for redirection (follow what is given in Figma), and note what is written below

||*Scenario*||*CTA Type*||*Redirection*||
|No products found|Add New|Add new product bottomsheet|
|One product found (bill or no bill)|Pay Now|Take to payment flow directly|
|More than one product found (but payability status for at least one product is FALSE)|Pay Now|Take to Pay Tab with Pay Together Toggle OFF|
|More than one product found (payability status for all products is TRUE)|Pay Together|Take to Pay Tab with Pay Together Toggle ON|

column31: Build the logic to fetch the subsequent refresh pull from Experian after 30 days of the previous pull.

column1: Restrict Addition of One CC per Customer
column31:
For every CC added by one customer, the same CC should not be added by another customer.



This can be implemented in either of these ways:

# When the customer enters the complete card number(while verifying or manual add), if the bene id for that already exist and linked to another customer, the same card should not be allowed to be added
# When the customer enters the complete card number(while verifying or manual add), create forward hash(which cannot be decrypted) and if the same forward hash exist for the same card, it should not be allowed to be added

column1: Repository for Credit Card Assets [Illustrations]
column31:
We need three assets for all credit cards:

||*Asset Type*||*Naming Convention*||
|Logo with Name|<id>-logo-with-name|
|Logo without Name|<id>-logo|
|Logo image ingrained in the Card|<id>-card-image|
|Color Code & Opacity levels (within card + on border)|{ 
"cardColor":"#000000", "opacity_border":"30%", "opacity_topLeft":"0%", "opacity_bottomRight":"12%" 
}
in [this sheet|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1sVNJT5w0sWDySG4f59hPPWImsFupCf_lZUFQ0qwu5UE/edit?usp=sharing] (Tab = BankMasters-New, Col = ui_config)|

For the generic/skeleton views where the above assets are not available, the naming convention to be with Id=9999

* Pick the id from [this sheet|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1sVNJT5w0sWDySG4f59hPPWImsFupCf_lZUFQ0qwu5UE/edit?usp=sharing] (Tab = BankMasters-New)
* Add the assets in the Google Drive [here|https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/108inAxeLXvSXSXPhbf0L868IKVVf-Wvr?usp=share_link] and cardColor and opacity levels in the sheet

column31:
Expectation in overall transactions ledger:

* If a Pay Together transaction is completed for 3 products, each of the three products will be shown as a separate entry in the ledger.
